<HEAD>Lawyers Settle Drought Lawsuit as Jury Rules In Favor Of Farmers</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN NOLAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Thousands of farmers who were originally denied drought insurance payments will split nearly $ 5 million in compensation under an out-of-court settlement. As lawyers agreed to the deal, a <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> jury awarded the farmers $ 40 million in damages. But the settlement reached out of the courtroom will stand. In all, the farmers and <ORGANIZATION> Chubb </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>, which joined them in their lawsuit against <ORGANIZATION> Good </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Weather </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, agreed to settle the suit for $ 8 million, the amount of the agent's liability insurance. The farmers will collect $ 4.93 million and the <ORGANIZATION> Chubb </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> insurance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> companies </ORGANIZATION> will collect $ 3.07 million. The verdict came on the jury's second day of deliberations. `` We're very excited. It's further proof that the farmers had really been taken advantage of,'' said <PERSON> Stanley </PERSON> <PERSON> Chesley </PERSON>, lawyer for the farmers. <PERSON> Chesley </PERSON> said the farmers _ 8,800 in 10 states _ should be receiving their money in about one week. He said a court-appointed lawyer will determine the amount farmers will receive. <ORGANIZATION> Chubb </ORGANIZATION>, of <LOCATION> Warren </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J. </LOCATION>, paid $ 53 million to settle farmers' claims against it, then joined the farmers' lawsuit against Good Weather, suing to demand $ 77 million in damages The farmers and <ORGANIZATION> Chubb </ORGANIZATION> claimed Good Weather sold more 1988 drought insurance than <ORGANIZATION> Chubb </ORGANIZATION> authorized. But Good Weather, based in <LOCATION> Syosset </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </L