<HEAD>Forest Fire Burns 300 Acres on Greek Resort Island</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RHODES, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A fire destroyed 300 acres of forest land on this popular resort island before it was brought under control Saturday. No injuries or property damage were reported. The wind-whipped fire started Friday evening in the central part of the island and spread quickly, the <ORGANIZATION> Forest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> said. Despite the efforts of two small firefighting planes and hundreds of firefighters, the blaze raged out of control through the night. As dawn approached, five more firefighting aircraft arrived from the mainland and together with 600 firefighters and soldiers they brought the fire under control at 10:15 a.m., the service said.
