RGANIZATION> Protection </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> administrator <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Ruckelshaus </PERSON> also had advice for lawmakers. <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON> called for more state spending to lower infant mortality and <PERSON> Skinner </PERSON> urged states to raise local gasoline taxes and spend more on highways. <PERSON> Ruckelshaus </PERSON>, now head of a large waste disposal company, said lawmakers should show more backbone in finding sites for solid waste landfills. Deputy Energy Secretary <PERSON> Henson </PERSON> <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> said his department will design a `` road map'' for a national energy policy, but said many of the policies must be implemented at the state level.
