<DATELINE>GALVESTON, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> ticketed six shrimpers for violating new trawling-time restrictions intended to keep sea turtles from drowning, authorities said Saturday. Five shrimpers in <LOCATION> Galveston </LOCATION> and one in <LOCATION> Freeport </LOCATION> were issued citations for trawling without turtle excluder devices during 30-minute restricted periods, said <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Don </PERSON> <PERSON> Merwin </PERSON>. The new regulations being rigorously enforced since Friday night require shrimpers to limit trawling to 105-minute intervals as outlined by a Coast Guard time chart or use the devices, which are designed to allow sea turtles to escape from shrimping nets. The devices are big boxes attached to nets with hinged sides that turtles can swim through. Shrimpers who elect not to use the devices have to pull their nets from the water during the 30-minute intervals when trawling is prohibited. `` I would think that a vessel that has its nets in the water during those periods will be a good candidate for boarding,'' <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Nicholas </PERSON> <PERSON> Sandifer </PERSON> said in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> has been broadcasting the time schedules and is warning shrimpers before each 30-minute ban goes into effect, <PERSON> Merwin </PERSON> said. Shrimpers out during the 30-minute intervals are being asked to pull in their nets for inspection. Those without the devices are fined. The maximum fine for a first and second offense is $ 8,000. The maximum fine for a third offense is $ 12,000. Fines are levied by the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marines </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fisheries </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Merwin </PERSON> said. The Coast Guard is patrolling areas from <LOCATION> Cameron </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> La. </LOCATION>, to <LOCATION> Freeport </LOCATION>. The order to enforce the limited trawling option was issued at 6 p.m. Thursday. Three hours later, the captain of a shrimping vessel off the <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> coast was cited after a <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> boarding crew observed that it was trawling illegally, <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> officials said. Shrimpers who have fought against using the excluder devices are concerned that the regulations implemented by <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Commerce Secretary <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Mosbacher </PERSON> are so complicated they will be hard to follow.
